st way to deploy and run applications on any existing Kubernetes cluster.","member_subcategory":"Silver"},{"category":"App Definition and Development","id":"app-definition-and-development--continuous-integration-delivery--cloudbees-codeship","name":"Cloudbees Codeship","logo":"logos/019cf5661461705a47102ae7469749efdd5f6c1204c36e50d784568a63475e7a.svg","subcategory":"Continuous Integration & Delivery","website":"https://www.cloudbees.com/products/codeship/overview","description":"Ship faster with CI/CD as a Service","member_subcategory":"Silver"},{"category":"App Definition and Development","id":"app-definition-and-development--continuous-integration-delivery--codefresh","name":"Codefresh","logo":"logos/ed018b580b480ee25ea29dcedccefdfc7594656d1d9ed31e15ef8038ba17a486.svg","subcategory":"Continuous Integration & Delivery","website":"https://codefresh.io/"},{"category":"App Definition and Development","id":"app-definition-and-development--continuous-integration-delivery--concourse","name":"Concourse","logo":"logos/2cb6c919a7701f840131a498256cf717f03491246eb79a24c44a8d83ef715894.svg","subcategory":"Continuous Integration & Delivery","website":"https://concourse-ci.org/","primary_repository_url":"https://github.com/concourse/concourse"},{"category":"App Definition and Development","id":"app-definition-and-development--continuous-integration-delivery--devtron","name":"Devtron","logo":"logos/b7beb143179fbd788439769e8529b7ceb54442d3fc5ef193d3028f85d73432a4.svg","subcategory":"Continuous Integration & Delivery","website":"https://devtron.ai","description":"Open source Software delivery workflow for Kubernetes","primary_repository_url":"https://github.com/devtron-labs/devtron"},{"category":"App Definition and Development","id":"app-definition-and-development--continuous-integration-delivery--flagger","name":"Flagger","logo":"logos/c28104b5a7bb3501d87865f60290d1ce3c79d7ccc36360624572b3ce904b1c2a.svg","subcategory":"Continuous Integration & Delivery","website":"https://docs.flagger.app","primary_repository_url":"https://github.com/fluxcd/flagger"},{"category":"App Definition and Development","id":"app-definition-and-development--continuous-integration-delivery--flux","name":"Flux","logo":"logos/c513f673e1c90ff7826a7aa6065452b4bade9bd731db2e05675b74d6f5940d49.svg","subcategory":"Continuous Integration & Delivery","website":"https://fluxcd.io/","maturity":"graduated","primary_repository_url":"https://github.com/fluxcd/flux2","tag":["app-delivery"]},{"category":"App Definition and Development","id":"app-definition-and-development--continuous-integration-delivery--fortio","name":"Fortio","logo":"logos/f2cbb9484bb193e51dd214344e1c3a2d1a21e0b320ca0765e0f2af6e6ae936ba.svg","subcategory":"Continuous Integration & Delivery","website":"https://fortio.org/","description":"Fortio is an open source load testing library, command-line tool, and server application written in Go. Originated as Istio's performance characterization tool (in particular proxy overhead), Fortio has evolved into a versatile tool for load testing and performance benchmarking of HTTP, gRPC, and TCP services. Among other options it enables users to generate a specified query-per-second (QPS) load and records detailed latency histograms, facilitating the analysis of performance metrics. The server component offers a straightforward web UI and REST API, allowing users to initiate tests and visualize results through graphical representations. Beyond load testing, Fortio provides server-side features akin to httpbin, including request echoing with headers, configurable latency or error responses, TCP echoing and proxying, HTTP fan-out, and support for gRPC echo and health checks. These capabilities make Fortio a versatile tool for debugging and testing high-performance services in cloud-native environments. As an organization set of git repositories, is also a growing set of reusable libraries for writing Cloud Native Go code and CLIs.","primary_repository_url":"https://github.com/fortio/fortio"},{"category":"App Definition and Development","id":"app-definition-and-development--continuous-integration-delivery--github-actions","name":"GitHub Actions","logo":"logos/544558e56e8ec6afb65343e46a37b8f59cc598bb747dc457be1806ad50424def.svg","subcategory":"Continuous Integration & Delivery","website":"https://github.com/features/actions","description":"GitHub Actions makes it easy to automate all your software workflows, now with world-class CI/CD. Build, test, and deploy your code right from GitHub. Make code reviews, branch management, and issue triaging work the way you want."},{"category":"App Definition and Development","id":"app-definition-and-development--continuous-integration-delivery--gitlab","name":"GitLab","logo":"logos/72e8d2db57539aabce0fbe6e0a044eba7142c7f4343922abb65f2fe04f1b8c84.svg","subcategory":"Continuous Integration & Delivery","website":"https://about.gitlab.com/","primary_repository_url":"https://github.com/gitlabhq/gitlabhq"},{"category":"App Definition and Development","id":"app-definition-and-development--continuous-integration-delivery--gitness","name":"Gitness","logo":"logos/8ca8bfce1e4c777979fec5b920a42efa39cf3a3c569c3fbd3f1afff745b032ef.svg","subcategory":"Continuous Integration & Delivery","website":"https://gitness.com/","member_subcategory":"Silver","primary_repository_url":"https://github.com/harness/gitness"},{"category":"App Definition and Development","id":"app-definition-and-development--continuous-integration-delivery--gocd","name":"GoCD","logo":"logos/6650e72dfb9e4973e5d7302aa64d0d4c2aa1c4853ea02ba942cc108176125698.svg","subcategory":"Continuous Integration & Delivery","website":"https://www.gocd.org/","primary_repository_url":"https://github.com/gocd/gocd"},{"category":"App Definition and Development","id":"app-definition-and-development--continuous-integration-delivery--google-cloud-build","name":"Google Cloud Build","logo":"logos/f2c27b69bc188ec89e96c3332226c73b43b29b82fc14ea076f7199d1b04570f4.svg","subcategory"